{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c3b5a8f6-d19d-45dc-b048-3287c29db4b3","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so here's how to do it yourself:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, easiest):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Then inside the interactive session:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n   - `pe` — print the last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary (useful for OOM)\n   - `threads` — list all managed threads\n   - `clrstack -all` — stacks for all threads\n\n2. **Visual Studio** (Windows): File → Open → File → select `.dmp` → \"Debug with Managed Only\"\n\n3. **`lldb` + SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   ```\n\n### Typical Analysis Flow\n\n1. Run `pe` to see if there's an unhandled exception\n2. Run `clrstack` to see what code was executing\n3. Run `threads` to check for deadlocks or thread pool starvation\n4. Run `dumpheap -stat` if you suspect memory issues\n\nWould you like me to walk you through running any of these commands on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"30820873-5ea2-4fc3-a09f-4402b1018a6a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says:\n\n\"USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps for CoreCLR or NativeAOT, capturing dumps from running .NET processes, setting up dump collection in Docker or Kubernetes, using dotnet-dump collect or createdump. DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing, or for .NET Framework processes.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill explicitly says NOT to use it for analyzing dumps. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":534,"requestId":"CB11:FB5EA:1F2273D:227511C:6A052B6B"},"id":"f8d90ce3-33da-472b-9fc4-eba1b9f596ad","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:55:06.953Z","parentId":"43f43394-e913-4c6b-a876-2c3968d8d3b0"}
